  "notes": "WebFetch tool was denied; used Playwright to load https://www.tasteatlas.com/detroit-style-pizza/wheretoeat. The page is a JS-rendered Angular SPA: the initial HTML is a 32KB shell containing only dish metadata (no restaurant list). The visible page also runs an auto-rotating carousel that swaps the URL between sibling pizza categories (apizza, pizza-al-taglio, chicago-pizza, new-york-style-pizza, traditional-italian-pizza), which made DOM scraping unreliable. Restaurant list is loaded via XHR to /api/v2/dishes/{dishId}/restaurants; the dish ID for Detroit-style pizza was found in the inline ta-app config as 1441. Calling that endpoint returned the full list of 10 restaurants (Count=10), which matches what the public 'where to eat' page displays. Per-restaurant 1-5 ratings are NOT exposed by this endpoint - only an internal AggregatedScore (e.g. 13050) and CriticCount. The dish itself carries Score.DividedScore=3.8/5 (Score.Score=7.62, ScoreCount=130), recorded at the top level. City vs. region: the 'city' field is taken from the parsed street address; 'region' is TasteAtlas's RegionName (often the metro area, e.g. 'Detroit' for Hazel Park). All 10 places are in the United States."
